theorem P3_closed_iff_open {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (hA : IsClosed A) :
    Topology.P3 A ↔ IsOpen A := by
  constructor
  · intro hP3
    -- Using `hP3` and `hA`, upgrade the containment to lie inside `interior A`.
    have hSub : (A : Set X) ⊆ interior A := by
      simpa [hA.closure_eq] using hP3
    -- Since `interior A ⊆ A`, we actually have equality.
    have hEq : interior A = A := by
      apply subset_antisymm
      · exact interior_subset
      · exact hSub
    -- An equality with its interior makes `A` open.
    simpa [hEq] using isOpen_interior
  · intro hOpen
    -- Show `A ⊆ interior (closure A)` using the facts that `A` is both open and closed.
    dsimp [Topology.P3]
    intro x hx
    -- Membership in an open set is the same as membership in its interior.
    have hxInt : x ∈ interior A := by
      simpa [hOpen.interior_eq] using hx
    -- Replace `closure A` by `A` because the latter is closed.
    simpa [hA.closure_eq] using hxInt

theorem P2_of_interior_closure_interior {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] (A : Set X) :
    Topology.P2 (interior (closure (interior A))) := by
  simpa using
    (Topology.P2_of_open (A := interior (closure (interior A))) isOpen_interior)
